<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="106">Mentum bearing paired foveae; anterior tibia with apicolateral notch; dorsal surface dull, with coarse, granulate microsculpture; head and eyes large; head and pronotum subequal in greatest width; pronotum round, subcordiform; pronotal hind angles tiny, laterally produced; i8 slightly bent around Eo5-6; ARG elongate, anterior hook laterally remote from 4th discal seta. ABL = 3.3-3.9 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="106" type="distribution">
